cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for predicting optical flow between two images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an unsupervised approach for training a convolutional neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning, specifically deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the use of loss functions and optimization techniques, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
